  "text": "Self-reported data were collected using the Barratt Impulsiveness Scale (BIS-11). [CITATION_1] A two-factor model was implemented to determine scores for cognitive and behavioral impulsivity, on the basis of a psychometric evaluation of the measure. [CITATION_2] According to the model, cognitive impulsivity reflects difficulties in attentional control, concentration, careful and deliberate thinking and planning, whereas behavioral impulsivity reflects impulsive action, racing thoughts and frequent changes in employment and residences. fMRI acquisition fMRI was performed on a 3-T Siemens Trio MRI system (Siemens Medical Solutions USA, Malvern, PA, USA), with 152 resting-state T2*-weighted, echoplanar images acquired (slice thickness = 4 mm; 34 slices; repetition time (TR) = 2 s; echo time (TE) = 30 ms; flip angle = 90°; matrix = 64 × 64; fov = 200 mm). Resting-state images were acquired for 5 min while participants viewed a black screen. High-resolution, T2-weighted, matchedbandwidth and T1-weighted magnetization-prepared rapid-acquisition gradient echo scans were also acquired. The orientation for these scans was oblique axial to maximize brain coverage and to optimize signal from ventromedial prefrontal cortex.",
